there's no question who
the leading philosopher

21:57.410 --> 22:00.880
of the 20th century
is, Hannah Arendt."

22:02.950 --> 22:04.520
Your work is mature.

22:03.690 --> 22:06.910
On the World of Values
in Hannah Arendt

22:04.520 --> 22:06.920
If you can double the
length of this paper,

22:06.920 --> 22:09.220
in terms of an
acceptable thesis,

22:10.330 --> 22:11.590
it would be considered well

22:11.590 --> 22:13.630
above the level
needed for passing.

22:13.630 --> 22:14.860
Uh, thank you.

22:14.860 --> 22:16.530
That being said,

22:16.530 --> 22:20.030
since you're capable of
such philosophical thought,

22:20.030 --> 22:23.740
I wonder if you're suited for
a pragmatic subject like law.

22:26.170 --> 22:29.940
Tell me, are you devoting
time to studying law?

22:31.110 --> 22:32.010
Uh-huh.

22:36.150 --> 22:37.780
Oh.

22:45.060 --> 22:47.730
It was like I was living
in a moment forever.

22:49.780 --> 22:51.200
My dearest

22:50.830 --> 22:52.600
I'm sorry. After you.

22:52.240 --> 22:56.910
Why don't we listen

22:54.470 --> 22:57.540
Oh, no, after you, I insist.

22:57.040 --> 23:00.330
For the voices of the wind?

22:57.540 --> 22:58.600
Here you go.

22:58.610 --> 22:59.570
I can't.

22:59.570 --> 23:00.840
It's okay.

23:01.080 --> 23:03.920
On a cold hill

23:02.440 --> 23:03.710
Thank you.

23:04.130 --> 23:06.920
In Umegaoka

23:07.380 --> 23:15.180
It blows from nowhere

23:16.100 --> 23:21.060
Telling me restlessly

23:21.560 --> 23:26.650
That our love may go astray

23:23.630 --> 23:26.770
Dear
Miss Chiaki Minase,

23:26.740 --> 23:27.570
My dearest...

23:27.650 --> 23:35.410
Why don't we
Listen for the voices of the wind

23:42.080 --> 23:47.300
See how vivid

23:47.920 --> 23:53.300
The lingering snow looks

23:53.890 --> 23:58.310
What blows over it

23:59.640 --> 24:04.820
Is an everlasting

24:05.400 --> 24:06.780
Gentle wind

24:06.860 --> 24:10.070
To Ms. Chiaki Minase

24:11.320 --> 24:19.330
Oh, there is something there

24:18.850 --> 24:21.050
"My dearest, why
don't we listen

24:20.160 --> 24:25.500
That looks trembling

24:21.060 --> 24:22.590
for the voices of the wind?

24:24.930 --> 24:29.030
On a cold hill on Umegaoka,
it blows from nowhere,

24:29.340 --> 24:34.090
Oh, my dearest

24:30.400 --> 24:34.130
telling me restlessly that
our love may go astray.

24:35.220 --> 24:38.430
It's too immature

24:36.000 --> 24:39.170
Why don't you listen for
the voices of the wind?"

24:38.560 --> 24:42.940
To call it love

24:43.810 --> 24:51.820
Yet it's too awkward to
Call it friendship

24:52.400 --> 24:57.580
Our hearts are

24:58.200 --> 25:06.210
At the mercy of the wind

25:09.800 --> 25:17.800
Out of nowhere it brings
An eternal feeling

25:19.010 --> 25:21.430
On the World of Values
in Hannah Arendt

25:21.520 --> 25:26.560
That resembles noble sadness

25:27.390 --> 25:31.760
"For Arendt, living humanely
and freely are the same thing.

25:34.360 --> 25:37.530
To live freely is to join
political activities.

25:39.500 --> 25:43.140
In other words, having political
freedom makes you human.

25:44.810 --> 25:47.970
If you don't have it,
you're living like an animal

25:47.980 --> 25:49.640
or a slave, at your core.

25:52.210 --> 25:54.050
After the rise of Marxism,

25:54.050 --> 25:56.250
the society gave
undeserved praise

25:56.250 --> 25:58.420
to labor as a political value.

26:00.520 --> 26:03.720
It's a shame that people are
now working like slaves."

26:06.960 --> 26:07.930
This is difficult.

26:12.370 --> 26:15.370
I understand exactly what
you're saying, Professor,

26:15.370 --> 26:18.240
but I don't agree with
your view on the Cold War.

26:18.240 --> 26:19.510
Honestly, I think your view

26:19.510 --> 26:21.210
- is completely wrong.
- Hey.

26:21.210 --> 26:22.110
Wow.

26:26.010 --> 26:28.150
Maybe you are right, Satoru.

26:28.150 --> 26:30.120
But it's not wise to
challenge the professor

26:30.120 --> 26:32.020
in front of the class like that.

26:32.020 --> 26:35.650
But there is no doubt that
communism will collapse soon.

26:35.660 --> 26:38.190
I just said what I
knew to be correct.

26:38.190 --> 26:41.030
Hey, criticizing the
professor's gonna hurt

26:41.030 --> 26:42.190
your grades, you know.

26:44.270 --> 26:48.000
They say that silence
goes further than eloquence.

26:48.000 --> 26:49.300
What?

26:49.300 --> 26:51.140
Too much talking
will cost you.

26:52.770 --> 26:56.180
I'm talking about you.

27:05.120 --> 27:06.720
I remember
the joy of walking

27:06.720 --> 27:07.990
in the summer evening.

27:09.860 --> 27:13.490
I loved being engrossed in
a book on a warm autumn day.

27:16.100 --> 27:18.630
I experienced such
happiness repeatedly.

27:22.510 --> 27:27.680
An Inquiry into the Good
by Kitaro Nishida

27:27.480 --> 27:30.610
You've been sending your
poems to Chiaki Minase?

27:30.610 --> 27:31.840
Are you serious?

27:31.850 --> 27:33.580
Mm-hmm, and I
sent her my paper

27:33.580 --> 27:35.610
on Hannah Arendt,
the other day, too.

27:35.620 --> 27:37.380
- Whoa.
- Seriously?

27:37.390 --> 27:39.790
You sent that out
of the blue to her?

27:39.790 --> 27:41.290
That's brave.

27:41.290 --> 27:43.190
When I read your paper, it
gave me such a headache.

27:44.630 --> 27:46.290
Yeah, I guess it's a little
difficult for you guys.

27:47.400 --> 27:48.990
Uh...

27:49.930 --> 27:51.200
Listen, Satoru.

27:52.530 --> 27:54.330
I think you're
making it difficult

27:54.340 --> 27:56.870
for Chiaki to respond to you.

27:56.870 --> 27:58.700
Well, that's not what I want,

27:58.710 --> 28:01.910
'cause to me, she's like a
personification of eternity.

28:02.780 --> 28:04.280
Uh-huh.

28:04.280 --> 28:07.110
I want her to never forget
that I existed in this world.

28:08.020 --> 28:09.550
That's all that I ask.

28:11.250 --> 28:13.790
Anyway, we'll
put in a good word

28:13.790 --> 28:16.960
to Chiaki for you,
as well.

28:27.580 --> 28:31.710
My dearest Chiaki

28:32.830 --> 28:37.960
Let's take a walk together quietly

28:38.630 --> 28:46.510
Let me hold the sleeve of your Yukata

28:47.180 --> 28:55.190
And tell you a fairy tale

29:00.360 --> 29:06.070
But you're looking away

29:06.490 --> 29:14.500
Watching only fireflies

29:20.460 --> 29:25.140
My dearest Chiaki

29:25.680 --> 29:30.930
At dusk of the early summer

29:31.480 --> 29:36.440
Putting my arm around your shoulder

29:37.110 --> 29:42.070
I never feel lonely

29:42.650 --> 29:47.910
Nothing makes me lonely

29:48.580 --> 29:50.830
I never

29:49.080 --> 29:52.480
Dear Satoru,
I am very sorry,

29:51.290 --> 29:53.580
Feel sad

29:54.020 --> 29:58.520
but I'm not the ideal woman
that you imagine I am.

29:54.160 --> 29:59.420
Nothing makes me sad

30:15.240 --> 30:19.780
Satoru, know that I think of it.

30:19.780 --> 30:22.310
Those letters were
letters for the future.

30:25.420 --> 30:29.790
Your 13 letters were filled
with clear yet eternal words.

30:32.430 --> 30:35.090
They were telling me to
remember you in your youth.

30:37.460 --> 30:41.170
Perhaps I was being tasked to
serve as your time capsule.

30:44.610 --> 30:46.000
Here you go!

30:46.010 --> 30:47.840
- Ah, just in time.
- Thank you.

30:47.840 --> 30:49.110
- Yours.
- Thanks.

30:51.480 --> 30:53.550
It was difficult to
see him heartbroken.

30:54.680 --> 30:57.550
And,
Kurosawa, what you said

30:57.550 --> 31:00.420
to him was unnecessary.

31:00.420 --> 31:03.690
Oh, yeah,
I felt bad about that.

31:03.690 --> 31:05.290
I just stoked his
competitive fire

31:05.290 --> 31:08.060
by telling him you're
not really a law student

31:08.060 --> 31:10.160
if you don't even try
to take the bar exam.

31:11.230 --> 31:12.260
Imagine my surprise

31:13.800 --> 31:16.400
when he suddenly started
studying for the exam really hard

31:16.400 --> 31:18.200
because of what I said.

31:18.210 --> 31:20.540
Yeah, I remember
that, even then,

31:20.540 --> 31:23.540
he was trying to find the
right path for himself.

31:23.540 --> 31:24.780
And it really seemed

31:24.780 --> 31:27.280
like college classes
were not a challenge.

31:27.280 --> 31:29.920
According to Karl
Popper, and I quote:

31:29.920 --> 31:32.450
Closed societies believe
in the unprovable,

31:32.450 --> 31:34.190
like gods and the afterlife.

31:34.190 --> 31:36.990
The society that's
free from superstition

31:36.990 --> 31:40.160
and believes in science
is an open society.

31:44.370 --> 31:46.230
A theory from the
empirical sciences-

31:46.230 --> 31:48.530
- What's the matter?

31:48.540 --> 31:49.400
Oh, nothing.

31:51.240 --> 31:54.110
Do you think that it's
acceptable to be teaching

31:54.110 --> 31:57.880
about atheist theory and
philosophy at a university level?

31:59.410 --> 32:01.210
Well, I'm a Christian myself.

32:02.020 --> 32:03.750
But to be honest,

32:03.750 --> 32:05.550
I don't get this
whole afterlife.

32:07.550 --> 32:08.450
I see.

32:10.120 --> 32:12.930
There might not be any
professor I can learn from here.

32:28.110 --> 32:33.120
Mock Bar Exam
Top student in April: Satoru Ichijo

32:34.200 --> 32:37.240
Mock Bar Exam
Top student in May: Satoru Ichijo

32:38.330 --> 32:41.870
Mock Bar Exam
Top student in June: Satoru Ichijo

32:40.020 --> 32:41.620
You failed?

32:41.620 --> 32:44.890
You got top score on the
exam six times in a row.

32:44.890 --> 32:46.120
Yeah.

32:46.130 --> 32:47.930
I passed the short
answer part easily,

32:47.930 --> 32:52.000
but then I criticized the
existing law in my essay.

32:52.000 --> 32:53.770
- You did that again?
- Huh?

32:53.770 --> 32:55.670
What did we tell you
about doing that on exams?

32:55.670 --> 32:57.200
You know you're gonna fail

32:57.200 --> 33:00.210
when you criticize existing
law on the exam like that.

33:00.210 --> 33:02.940
Though I didn't pass
the essay part, either.

33:04.410 --> 33:06.910
It's just that I
can't help myself

33:06.910 --> 33:10.220
but to point out what
is ideologically wrong.

33:12.690 --> 33:15.520
So what are you
going to do now?

33:16.620 --> 33:18.390
You want to be a professor.

33:18.390 --> 33:20.260
You should continue
here at the lab.

33:20.260 --> 33:23.660
But you've read
like 1,400 books.

33:23.660 --> 33:25.660
Are you okay not staying here?

33:27.000 --> 33:29.670
Political science and
jurisprudence can't teach us

33:29.670 --> 33:31.240
what's right and what's wrong.

33:32.340 --> 33:37.110
I'd rather unify all the
different philosophies

33:37.110 --> 33:40.410
and create a new ideology
that will last forever.

33:43.620 --> 33:45.180
Not sure what you mean,

33:46.490 --> 33:48.190
but it doesn't sound you're
lookin' to land a job,

33:48.190 --> 33:50.190
at least not right away.

33:50.190 --> 33:52.060
But you are going to work
somewhere, aren't you?

33:52.060 --> 33:53.530
Mm-hmm.

33:53.530 --> 33:56.930
For starters, I'm gonna look
for a job near my house.

33:57.730 --> 33:59.460
- What?
- Huh?

33:59.470 --> 34:00.900
Remember how worried we were

34:00.900 --> 34:02.300
when he said he was
joining a trading company?

34:02.300 --> 34:03.570
- That's right.
- Oh, yeah!

34:03.570 --> 34:05.370
And he doesn't even
drink or play mahjong.

34:05.370 --> 34:06.810
With the professor's referral,

34:06.810 --> 34:09.340
he could've been at the
Maicho paper or Bank of Japan.

34:09.340 --> 34:10.280
- Ah!
- Such a waste!

34:10.280 --> 34:11.780
Didn't he say,

34:11.780 --> 34:13.949
"I want to test myself by
starting out from zero?"

34:13.949 --> 34:15.310
Yeah.

34:15.320 --> 34:16.880
Well, I guess he did really.

34:16.880 --> 34:18.719
In the end, it looks
like everything happened

34:18.719 --> 34:20.350
just the way it was supposed to.

34:20.350 --> 34:21.820
With a law degree.

34:21.820 --> 34:24.820
Mr. Ichijo started working
for the Toho Trading Company,

34:24.830 --> 34:27.989
only to leave at age 30
to establish Taiyoukai.

34:29.400 --> 34:32.100
I'm less than optimistic
about our future.

34:32.100 --> 34:33.000
Yes.

34:34.370 --> 34:37.300
If only he was still here
to get us through this.

34:37.300 --> 34:39.370
Hmm? Him, huh?

34:40.840 --> 34:41.909
What's done is done.

34:41.909 --> 34:43.010
Nothing we can do.

34:44.139 --> 34:46.750
I should've paid
better attention.

34:46.750 --> 34:48.080
Me as well.

34:50.750 --> 34:52.320
I'm just as guilty.

34:52.320 --> 34:53.880
I'm the one who insisted that
we absolutely had to hire him.

34:53.889 --> 34:55.449
I feel exactly the same.

34:58.530 --> 34:59.960
At his job interview,

34:59.960 --> 35:03.500
I tested his patience by
speaking way too harshly to him.

35:04.670 --> 35:06.230
But he didn't even flinch.

35:07.570 --> 35:08.970
Look at you.

35:08.970 --> 35:10.840
You're the public servant type.

35:10.840 --> 35:13.270
You're not suited to
work for a trading house.

35:14.610 --> 35:17.080
You rarely come
across a young man

35:17.080 --> 35:18.710
as tough as he was.

35:18.710 --> 35:21.050
I take it that's
why you called upon me

35:21.050 --> 35:22.550
to recruit him personally, huh?

35:23.980 --> 35:26.020
At that time, he was...

35:31.230 --> 35:32.260
Mr. Goto.

35:37.800 --> 35:41.030
Why the pinstripes?

35:44.740 --> 35:46.300
I really like it.

35:46.310 --> 35:48.810
Oh, so you are Satoru Ichijo?

35:50.210 --> 35:52.810
We are actually looking for
unique individuals like you.

35:54.050 --> 35:56.350
It might sound unusual
for a Tomei graduate

35:56.350 --> 35:58.650
with a law degree
to be a trader,

35:58.650 --> 36:01.720
but you see, I graduated
from Tomei like you.

36:04.120 --> 36:07.890
Then tell me, why did
you decide to work here?

36:07.900 --> 36:09.830
Weren't you offered other
professional choices,

36:09.830 --> 36:11.100
like banking maybe?

36:11.100 --> 36:12.800
Mr. Ichijo, that's no way

36:12.800 --> 36:14.070
- to speak to a-
- Ah, it's all right.

36:14.070 --> 36:14.970
Ah.

36:15.900 --> 36:17.670
Why did I choose to work here?

36:19.610 --> 36:21.940
Banking is mentally stimulating.

36:21.940 --> 36:23.540
That's for sure.

36:23.540 --> 36:25.010
But trading's more than that.

36:25.010 --> 36:28.710
It's also stimulating,
but you can dream big.

36:29.580 --> 36:30.480
Dream big?

36:32.750 --> 36:35.090
Obviously, you're intelligent.

36:35.090 --> 36:37.560
But at the same time,

36:37.560 --> 36:38.620
you're a dreamer.

36:39.930 --> 36:43.600
Someone like you should
come work in trading.

36:45.730 --> 36:48.830
Intelligent and a dreamer.

36:51.000 --> 36:51.900
Hmm?

36:53.670 --> 36:57.040
Ichijo, we'd be honored

36:57.040 --> 36:59.180
to have your talents
at our company.

37:01.380 --> 37:05.880
Mr. Goto, please, you
don't have to do that.

37:41.220 --> 37:43.630
Happiness Essays by Carl Hilty

37:48.000 --> 37:50.000
I want to be a
thinker, after all.

37:51.930 --> 37:54.570
With graduation drawing near,

37:54.570 --> 37:56.600
I could feel my passion growing.

38:03.480 --> 38:04.880
Ooh, ooh, ooh!

38:05.810 --> 38:09.710
Ooh!

38:13.890 --> 38:14.790
All right.

38:16.920 --> 38:19.120
Got a good haul today,
didn't we?

38:22.630 --> 38:24.730
Satoru, what's wrong?

38:33.710 --> 38:38.780
The life of a
fish is fragile or transient.

38:52.930 --> 38:56.800
I should look back on my
life and reflect on that.

38:59.900 --> 39:01.170
When I read your paper,

39:01.170 --> 39:02.600
it gave me such a
headache.

39:02.600 --> 39:04.940
Yeah, I guess it's a little
difficult for you guys.

39:09.080 --> 39:11.740
Mom must be relieved and
happy if you're around.

39:14.280 --> 39:16.920
Seriously, you need
to look after Mom more,

39:16.920 --> 39:18.280
while I'm away.

39:18.290 --> 39:19.550
Your school's nearby.

39:20.920 --> 39:22.950
Oh, oh, yeah, sorry.

39:25.790 --> 39:27.030
Why did I say things

39:27.030 --> 39:29.030
that hurt other
people's feelings?

39:30.730 --> 39:34.270
When did I throw away
their acts of kindness?

39:35.970 --> 39:38.200
Where does this
selfishness come from?

39:41.270 --> 39:44.410
God forbid, if anything
happens to your father,

39:44.410 --> 39:46.240
I want you to know this.

39:47.350 --> 39:49.410
Don't worry about us.

39:49.420 --> 39:51.180
We'll be just fine, okay?

39:52.290 --> 39:55.020
If you wanna study,
you can work part-time

39:55.020 --> 39:58.360
and still be able to
go to graduate school.

39:58.360 --> 40:00.690
Satoru is a really good guy.

40:00.690 --> 40:02.130
He's just super honest

40:02.130 --> 40:03.560
- and straightforward.
- Uh-huh.

40:03.560 --> 40:05.060
So pretty please.

40:05.070 --> 40:08.200
Could you please answer
his letters, just once?

40:08.200 --> 40:11.970
Father, Mother, my friends,

40:13.910 --> 40:16.340
I've been given so
much in my life,

40:20.880 --> 40:24.380
but all I was focused
on was my own success.

40:26.490 --> 40:28.850
When did I ever
cast aside my needs,

40:28.860 --> 40:32.320
and just how much have I ever
devoted myself to others?

40:37.200 --> 40:40.030
Once more, want to restart,

40:41.740 --> 40:43.470
want to be reborn.

40:53.250 --> 40:57.280
I can say that that was when
I experienced my first death.

40:59.220 --> 41:01.890
It meant that I had
to bury my false self.

41:08.590 --> 41:12.970
March 23, 1981

41:27.710 --> 41:30.680
Is someone trying to
tell me something?

41:39.660 --> 41:40.560
What?

41:44.880 --> 41:49.880
Good news.

41:59.710 --> 42:00.780
Good news?

42:00.780 --> 42:01.850
Is it like the Gospel
in Christianity?

42:09.090 --> 42:10.490
Who are you?

42:10.490 --> 42:11.460
Tell me your name.

42:18.660 --> 42:21.450
Nikko.

42:22.140 --> 42:23.030
Nikko?

42:26.410 --> 42:28.070
The first spirit to contact me

42:28.070 --> 42:32.780
by automatic writing was the
monk Nichiren's disciple Nikko.

42:35.580 --> 42:39.580
On that day, my life was
completely turned around.

42:44.290 --> 42:47.360
One week later, Nichiren
started contacting me.

42:51.060 --> 42:52.330
Please tell me.

42:52.330 --> 42:54.230
What am I supposed
to do with my life?

43:08.880 --> 43:14.260
Love people, nurture people,
and forgive people.

43:14.190 --> 43:19.260
Love people, nurture
people, and forgive people.

43:21.960 --> 43:24.530
So this means this is my mission

43:24.530 --> 43:27.100
and what I have to
accomplish in this lifetime.

43:28.570 --> 43:30.070
From now on,

43:30.070 --> 43:34.470
you're going to prove the
existence of the afterworld.

43:31.440 --> 43:34.230
Nichiren

43:34.470 --> 43:39.410
Your work will bring happiness
to all people in this world.

43:45.890 --> 43:48.450
I do understand what
you're telling me.

43:48.460 --> 43:53.520
But I, I'm not sure if I'm
ready to do such a mission now.

43:54.660 --> 43:57.200
I think, at first, I
need more experience

43:57.200 --> 43:59.230
and to establish my
professional career.

44:00.170 --> 44:02.100
I understand.

44:02.100 --> 44:04.900
My task is to
herald the beginning

44:04.900 --> 44:07.110
of your spiritual communication.

44:08.810 --> 44:12.880
You'll be visited by
various other spirits soon.

44:22.820 --> 44:25.540
Socrates

44:24.190 --> 44:26.220
This is how
I learned of my mission

44:26.230 --> 44:28.790
to spread the truth about
the spiritual world.

44:48.050 --> 44:50.550
Does this mean that more
than half of them are

44:50.550 --> 44:53.020
under the influence
of evil spirits?

45:06.370 --> 45:08.950
You are right.

45:11.100 --> 45:13.600
How can they protect themselves?

45:32.430 --> 45:34.960
The law of the same wavelength?

45:34.960 --> 45:37.700
So their state of mind
attracts evil spirits.

